{"title":"Portrait of a Figure near Water","author":{"name":"Jane Kenyon"},"publishDate":"2011-10-02","lines":[{"line":"Rebuked, she turned and ran","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"uphill to the barn. Anger, the inner","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"arsonist, held a match to her brain.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"She observed her life: against her will","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"it survived the unwavering flame.","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"The barn was empty of animals.","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"Only a swallow tilted","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"near the beams, and bats","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"hung from the rafters","stanza":2,"number":9},{"line":"the roof sagged between.","stanza":2,"number":10},{"line":"Her breath became steady","stanza":3,"number":11},{"line":"where, years past, the farmer cooled","stanza":3,"number":12},{"line":"the big tin amphorÃ¦ of milk.","stanza":3,"number":13},{"line":"The stone trough was still","stanza":3,"number":14},{"line":"filled with water: she watched it","stanza":3,"number":15},{"line":"and received its calm.","stanza":3,"number":16},{"line":"So it is when we retreat in anger:","stanza":4,"number":17},{"line":"we think we burn alone","stanza":4,"number":18},{"line":"and there is no balm.","stanza":4,"number":19},{"line":"Then water enters, though it makes","stanza":4,"number":20},{"line":"no sound.","stanza":4,"number":21}]}